1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,300
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,600
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:05,800
(Episode 19)

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,433
How could the team manager
suddenly be dead? What happened?

5
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:12,233
No way. That can't be true.

6
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,493
This is a fail.

7
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:22,533
Team Manager!

8
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,433
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, what are you doing here?

9
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:28,173
What are you doing here right now?

10
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,947
I was so shocked
when I heard you were dead!

11
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:33,219
What? I'm dead?

12
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:38,301
So you're the young lady
I talked to earlier.

13
00:00:38,859 --> 00:00:42,211
He already died a long time ago, at cards.

14
00:00:42,557 --> 00:00:44,293
So when you said he was dead,

15
00:00:44,573 --> 00:00:46,752
you meant he lost at Go-Stop?

16
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:48,635
Seriously.

17
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,555
What exactly were you thinking?

18
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,133
Freeze.

19
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:58,688
Where do you think you're going?

20
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:03,033
I can't even play
and I'm just slowing everyone down,

21
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:04,525
so I'll get going.

22
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,187
Even if you leave,
you finish this round first.

23
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,677
Or bring someone to play in your place.

24
00:01:21,936 --> 00:01:23,589
Me? Go!

25
00:01:23,589 --> 00:01:25,795
Yes! Three-go!

26
00:01:26,293 --> 00:01:27,931
Sorry, I wasn't planning...

27
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:29,827
to go for Godori.

28
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:36,701
Yes! It's a double hit.

29
00:01:36,701 --> 00:01:39,648
Give me one junk card each, please.

30
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,413
Where did you find this card shark?

31
00:01:42,696 --> 00:01:45,427
Five Brights, Godori, Chodan,

32
00:01:45,427 --> 00:01:47,853
22 junk cards, and 6 ribbon cards.

33
00:01:48,164 --> 00:01:49,531
And since I shook, it's double.

34
00:01:49,741 --> 00:01:50,952
And both of you...

35
00:01:50,952 --> 00:01:54,229
got gwang bak and pi bak, so 896 points.

36
00:01:54,427 --> 00:01:56,200
The last round was void,

37
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,144
so that doubles too.

38
00:01:58,356 --> 00:01:59,956
- Then...
- 1,792 points.

39
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:06,035
I'll just take 1.70 dollars each,
nice and clean.

40
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,739
Hey there, young man.
Don't just stand there.

41
00:02:10,112 --> 00:02:12,012
I'm hungry, go make some ramyeon.

42
00:02:12,821 --> 00:02:14,040
It's already been three hours.

43
00:02:14,492 --> 00:02:16,359
Your girl must be hungry too.

44
00:02:16,359 --> 00:02:17,992
What? My girl?

45
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:19,633
No, she's not my girl.

46
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:22,301
Grandma, I have high standards.

47
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,177
All right. This is the last round.

48
00:02:28,177 --> 00:02:29,395
No bottom-deck dealing.

49
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,800
Last round?

50
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,539
Are you trying to run off
after taking all my money?

51
00:02:34,537 --> 00:02:37,070
I may hop like a rabbit,

52
00:02:37,273 --> 00:02:38,500
but run off?

53
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,080
I'm a proper office worker.

54
00:02:40,372 --> 00:02:42,239
Should I really be doing this
during work hours?

55
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:45,256
I told you to make ramyeon.
Why are you standing there?

56
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,293
There's ramyeon and a pot inside,

57
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:50,213
so hurry up.

58
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,488
Okay...

59
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,500
Add green onions and eggs,

60
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,643
and keep the noodles firm.

61
00:03:00,752 --> 00:03:02,852
(Kangsu Construction)

62
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,533
- Good work.
- Good work.

63
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:12,333
- Let's go eat.
- By the way...

64
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,400
that lady hasn't shown up at all lately.

65
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,433
Who?

66
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,541
That real estate lady?

67
00:03:18,755 --> 00:03:19,837
Licensed realtor.

68
00:03:19,837 --> 00:03:21,200
Same thing.

69
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,893
Honestly, I can finally breathe
now that she's gone.

70
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,700
Why, do you miss her?

71
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,275
Who says I miss her?

72
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,965
She was working so hard,

73
00:03:28,965 --> 00:03:31,100
and she suddenly hasn't shown up for days,
so I was curious.

74
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:32,900
You're curious about the strangest things.

75
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:40,011
I'm stopping by my husband's office first.

76
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,048
What about you?
Are you going to meet your husband?

77
00:03:42,845 --> 00:03:45,928
My husband hates that kind of thing.

78
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,419
These days, your husband...

79
00:03:48,419 --> 00:03:50,155
practically comes to our house every day.

80
00:03:51,035 --> 00:03:54,643
Do you know what he's doing
with Father these days?

81
00:03:55,517 --> 00:03:56,643
How would I know?

82
00:03:57,096 --> 00:03:59,233
He never talks about work at home.

83
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:03,000
But he seems really busy.

84
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,300
He stays in the study until late at night.

85
00:04:05,576 --> 00:04:06,576
Really?

86
00:04:09,048 --> 00:04:11,880
Mr. Ju,
how many years has it been with me?

87
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,720
Excuse me?

88
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,800
Since I was ten years old,

89
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:20,160
so about 59 years?

90
00:04:20,733 --> 00:04:22,299
No, not that...

91
00:04:22,733 --> 00:04:24,400
I mean working as my secretary.

92
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,800
Well, since the year after you
were promoted to president,

93
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,747
it's been 15 years. But why do you ask?

94
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:31,933
That's quite a long time.

95
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,971
Wait.

96
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,033
You've lived in our side room
since before I was born,

97
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:39,408
so why 59 years?

98
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,677
It's been 61 years.

99
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,033
Sixty-one years.

100
00:04:45,744 --> 00:04:47,573
Right, 61 years.

101
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:53,653
But why are you suddenly asking that?

102
00:04:53,933 --> 00:04:55,715
Mr. Ju,

103
00:04:55,715 --> 00:05:01,433
I've been thinking
about reorganizing my staff.

104
00:05:02,059 --> 00:05:05,300
Don't tell me you're firing me.

105
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:07,744
No, that's not it.

106
00:05:07,744 --> 00:05:10,517
You're getting older, and I thought...

107
00:05:10,517 --> 00:05:13,400
maybe being my personal secretary
might be too much for you.

108
00:05:14,589 --> 00:05:18,288
Thank you for your concern,
but don't worry.

109
00:05:18,563 --> 00:05:22,035
I'm still going strong.

110
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,872
And the Chairman specifically told me...

111
00:05:25,872 --> 00:05:28,040
to take good care of you.

112
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,133
Mr. Ju... No.

113
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:33,424
Yong Man, let me be honest.

114
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:34,976
Well...

115
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:38,133
I need a brain.

116
00:05:38,133 --> 00:05:41,360
Not just someone
who protects me physically and mentally,

117
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,133
but someone sharp in business,

118
00:05:43,133 --> 00:05:45,712
someone professional
I can discuss management with.

119
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:49,272
That kind of secretary.

120
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:53,533
Then get the Chairman's approval first.

121
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:57,344
Other than the Chairman,
no one can fire me.

122
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,827
Unbelievable.

123
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:03,440
That guy... You're unbelievable!

124
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,171
Wait, hold on...

125
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,832
How can someone be that clueless?

126
00:06:09,408 --> 00:06:11,163
There has to be an opening

127
00:06:11,163 --> 00:06:12,800
before I can bring Seong Jun in.

128
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,571
Seriously.

129
00:06:14,866 --> 00:06:16,533
- Honey.
- Hey.

130
00:06:17,384 --> 00:06:18,384
- Honey.
- Yes?

131
00:06:18,384 --> 00:06:20,637
What brings you to the office?

132
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,352
I stopped by after line dancing class.

133
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:26,635
Honey, Seung Ri's mom was saying

134
00:06:26,635 --> 00:06:28,827
that even at home these days,

135
00:06:28,827 --> 00:06:30,576
Mr. Seo works late into the night.

136
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:34,480
Work? But what kind?

137
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:37,307
She doesn't know.
He always keeps his mouth shut.

138
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:41,539
Father has practically stepped back
from work,

139
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,691
so what could be keeping him so busy?

140
00:06:43,998 --> 00:06:46,365
Honey,

141
00:06:46,953 --> 00:06:49,953
don't get too involved in company matters.

142
00:06:50,637 --> 00:06:53,200
You should just stay
elegant and beautiful...

143
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,152
What am I, some decorative flower?

144
00:06:55,739 --> 00:06:57,800
I majored in French literature.

145
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:01,752
I'm someone who lives
like the dramatic heroine of my own story.

146
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:07,700
Where did Ms. Cho Eun Ae go?
I haven't seen her all afternoon.

147
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,389
When I got back from the archive room
after lunch, she wasn't at her desk.

148
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,627
Maybe she went out with the team manager.

149
00:07:16,806 --> 00:07:17,806
The ramyeon's ready.

150
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:19,907
Let's take a break.

151
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:22,600
Let's eat first.
Food comes before anything else.

152
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,600
- Right, eating is what matters.
- Please come this way.

153
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,200
Looks good.

154
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,033
What did you do to the noodles?

155
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,400
- What?
- I told you to keep them firm.

156
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,633
- They're all soggy.
- Then don't eat it.

157
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:40,133
The more I look at it,
the more she's too good for you.

158
00:07:41,016 --> 00:07:43,405
You can't play cards,
you can't make ramyeon.

159
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:45,133
What are you talking about?

160
00:07:45,233 --> 00:07:47,323
He's much better.

161
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:51,600
Did the young lady do nothing
but play cards?

162
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:53,700
Actually, when I was little,

163
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,048
the neighborhood grandpas and grandmas...

164
00:07:56,048 --> 00:07:57,400
gave me some early education.

165
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,635
Early education in Go-Stop.

166
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:02,300
I was once called a genius card shark.

167
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,867
- A genius card shark?
- A genius card shark?

168
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:07,133
What nonsense.

169
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,400
We got played.

170
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,400
We got played.

171
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,333
No wonder.

172
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,224
She's sly like a fox.

173
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,600
Come again tomorrow.

174
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:27,504
I need to win back
my precious 1.70 dollars.

175
00:08:28,149 --> 00:08:29,819
Grandma, I can't come tomorrow.

176
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:31,500
I'll return the coins instead.

177
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,500
No way.

178
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:37,320
I'll win that money back fair and square,
just so you know.

179
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:40,931
If you want this back,
come again tomorrow.

180
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,572
Grandma.

181
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:45,000
Please give that back.

182
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,900
She can't get into the company without it.

183
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:50,003
That's why I said come tomorrow.

184
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,333
(Maeseong Village Senior Center,
beware of dog)

185
00:09:05,832 --> 00:09:06,832
Do you hate dogs?

186
00:09:07,321 --> 00:09:10,121
Who said I hate them?
I just don't want to get bitten.

187
00:09:10,364 --> 00:09:11,964
"Beware of dog."

188
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:16,520
He likes people this much.
Why would he bite?

189
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,100
If he bit people, he wouldn't be here.

190
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Such a coward.

191
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,424
Coward?

192
00:09:22,424 --> 00:09:24,349
I got bitten by a dog when I was little.

193
00:09:24,539 --> 00:09:28,072
Dogs judge people too, so I get it.

194
00:09:29,765 --> 00:09:31,514
Doggy, what's your name?

195
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:34,900
Huindung? Happy? Dokgu?

196
00:09:37,309 --> 00:09:40,539
How are you this sweet?

197
00:09:40,949 --> 00:09:43,368
Such a gentle little thing.

198
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,285
You weren't taking pictures of me,
were you?

199
00:09:49,285 --> 00:09:52,169
Don't flatter yourself.
I was taking pictures of the dog.

200
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:57,200
Now explain yourself. What is going on?

201
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:01,048
Your outside work is coming here
to play cards and take pictures?

202
00:10:01,259 --> 00:10:02,892
Why? Is that a problem?

203
00:10:03,496 --> 00:10:06,000
Team Manager,
is now really the time for this?

204
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,581
Team One already has their concept,

205
00:10:08,757 --> 00:10:11,590
and they're already integrating Joy
with IoT.

206
00:10:12,249 --> 00:10:14,813
They think they can mess with my Joy!

207
00:10:15,019 --> 00:10:17,557
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
you're lacking in many ways,

208
00:10:17,785 --> 00:10:19,918
but patience is what you lack most.

209
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:23,043
What? Lacking in many ways?

210
00:10:23,043 --> 00:10:24,328
I told you to wait.

211
00:10:24,328 --> 00:10:26,493
This is work too.

212
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,800
Let's go.
If we leave now, it'll be quitting time.

213
00:10:33,372 --> 00:10:34,372
Forget it.

214
00:10:40,169 --> 00:10:41,669
You came here on a scooter?

215
00:10:42,197 --> 00:10:45,564
Yes, this is my trusty ride for commuting.

216
00:10:47,164 --> 00:10:48,464
Where's your car?

217
00:10:48,464 --> 00:10:50,939
I don't have one. I took the bus.

218
00:10:51,269 --> 00:10:54,779
What? You're a third-generation heir
and you don't have a car?

219
00:10:55,003 --> 00:10:56,752
Are you going to keep mocking me?

220
00:10:56,752 --> 00:10:59,088
That "rich heir" label
is what I hate hearing most.

221
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,048
What are you, Hong Gil Dong?

222
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:03,176
I can't even call a rich heir a rich heir?

223
00:11:07,827 --> 00:11:09,927
Get on.

224
00:11:10,283 --> 00:11:11,464
Get on?

225
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,600
Are you telling me to ride behind you?

226
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,155
It's almost rush hour.

227
00:11:18,371 --> 00:11:21,845
If you take the bus, I'm not sure
you'd make it home before midnight.

228
00:11:24,066 --> 00:11:26,233
I'll drop you off at the BS.

229
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:28,077
BS? What's that?

230
00:11:28,912 --> 00:11:30,621
The bus stop.

231
00:11:30,621 --> 00:11:32,163
Did you come from the moon or something?

232
00:11:33,456 --> 00:11:35,987
Bye, doggy. Be good.

233
00:11:38,699 --> 00:11:40,203
Slow down a little.

234
00:11:40,693 --> 00:11:43,077
I can't breathe. Ease up a bit.

235
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,123
I said slow down!

236
00:12:01,351 --> 00:12:02,584
- Team Manager.
- Yes?

237
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:04,243
We're here.

238
00:12:05,172 --> 00:12:06,572
We're here?

239
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,900
I survived.

240
00:12:10,048 --> 00:12:12,752
Aren't you getting off?
Let go of my waist.

241
00:12:15,779 --> 00:12:17,307
Were you a race car driver or something?

242
00:12:17,307 --> 00:12:18,888
Why are you riding that scooter
so aggressively?

243
00:12:19,379 --> 00:12:21,608
What? I followed the speed limit
the whole way.

244
00:12:21,608 --> 00:12:23,525
And you said you'd only take me
to the bus stop.

245
00:12:23,525 --> 00:12:24,725
Why didn't you stop there?

246
00:12:24,725 --> 00:12:25,900
There were buses lined up,

247
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,645
so there wasn't anywhere to stop.

248
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:30,123
I get you here quickly and safely,
and you still complain.

249
00:12:31,059 --> 00:12:32,347
My employee ID.

250
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,549
Take responsibility.

251
00:12:34,549 --> 00:12:36,357
Well, who told you
to be so good at Go-Stop?

252
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:38,900
What are you doing here?

253
00:12:40,127 --> 00:12:41,127
Are you getting off work now?

254
00:12:52,741 --> 00:12:54,887
So I guess you're going out
on field work together now?

255
00:12:55,456 --> 00:12:56,956
That's quite an improvement, Intern Cho.

256
00:12:57,279 --> 00:12:58,712
It just happened.

257
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:02,200
Sorry I couldn't tell you in advance,
Manager.

258
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,300
I had to leave in a hurry.

259
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:04,833
Why are you apologizing to me?

260
00:13:05,089 --> 00:13:07,456
Your direct supervisor is Team Manager Ko.

261
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,100
Since we're all here,

262
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:12,992
why don't we all go have dinner together?

263
00:13:13,203 --> 00:13:14,700
What? Dinner?

264
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:16,400
We just had a team dinner not long ago.

265
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,037
This isn't a team dinner.
It's team bonding.

266
00:13:20,259 --> 00:13:22,933
A bonding dinner for the key members
of Teams One and Two.

267
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:25,533
- Where should we go?
- What?

268
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:27,720
Then Ms. Cho Eun Ae can decide.

269
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,500
What? Me?

270
00:13:29,781 --> 00:13:31,048
Do you have somewhere in mind?

271
00:13:31,301 --> 00:13:33,139
A place that's tasty, comfortable,
and your favorite.

272
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,565
Cho Rong!

273
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:39,115
Welcome.

274
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:41,414
Team Manager, you're here again?

275
00:13:41,414 --> 00:13:42,414
Yes.

276
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,427
You were here before?

277
00:13:45,547 --> 00:13:48,003
When I dropped Ms. Cho Eun Ae off
after the team dinner.

278
00:13:48,219 --> 00:13:50,037
My house is right nearby.

279
00:13:51,053 --> 00:13:52,053
Please sit first.

280
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,833
- Sit down.
- Let's sit.

281
00:13:54,469 --> 00:13:55,469
Sit.

282
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:02,552
These must be Eun Ae's co-workers.

283
00:14:02,552 --> 00:14:04,696
Yes. This is the Chief Planning Officer,

284
00:14:04,696 --> 00:14:06,101
the Manager, and the Team Manager.

285
00:14:06,101 --> 00:14:09,200
Eun Ae is like my own granddaughter,

286
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,173
- so please take good care of her.
- Of course.

287
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:14,360
Let me take your order first.

288
00:14:14,444 --> 00:14:15,777
What would you like?

289
00:14:16,027 --> 00:14:18,627
That thing we had last time was good.

290
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,533
Right.

291
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,000
- Grandma, four bindaetteok.
- Okay.

292
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,437
- And with bindaetteok?
- Makgeolli?

293
00:14:25,437 --> 00:14:28,579
That's right.
Bindaetteok goes with makgeolli.

294
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:32,977
You two are really in sync.

295
00:14:33,731 --> 00:14:36,075
So you two went for a third round
that night?

296
00:14:36,304 --> 00:14:38,136
Not two, three.

297
00:14:39,659 --> 00:14:42,464
Thinking about how I got dragged here
against my will...

298
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,700
Let's start with a drink first.

299
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,549
Our Chief Planning Officer.

300
00:14:47,195 --> 00:14:48,428
Our Manager.

301
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,600
Team Manager.

302
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:54,616
Manager Seo.

303
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:57,683
What are you doing by yourself?

304
00:15:03,857 --> 00:15:04,957
I heard from Mom.

305
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:08,043
The foundation asked for a donation?

306
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,900
I'm sorry.
Ji Seon shouldn't have said anything.

307
00:15:13,603 --> 00:15:16,107
Don't tell me you're thinking the same...

308
00:15:16,107 --> 00:15:18,040
as Mom and Ji Seon.

309
00:15:18,718 --> 00:15:19,985
Of course not.

310
00:15:21,132 --> 00:15:24,532
But what is right
for philosopher Cho Eun Hyeong...

311
00:15:25,177 --> 00:15:27,477
Is it also right for Bit Na's father?

312
00:15:28,353 --> 00:15:29,753
I wonder
if this is really the best choice.

313
00:15:31,481 --> 00:15:32,681
Why did you hide it?

314
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,560
What? Hide what?

315
00:15:36,133 --> 00:15:38,800
That you lost your job.
It's already been a year.

316
00:15:39,733 --> 00:15:40,800
Did Eun Ae tell you?

317
00:15:41,883 --> 00:15:43,516
Eun Ae knew?

318
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,933
I found out today
when I went to your company.

319
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,600
I'm sorry.
I have no excuse as your father.

320
00:15:51,248 --> 00:15:53,348
Why are you sorry?
I'm the one who should be sorry.

321
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,433
As the eldest son,
I can't even take care of myself.

322
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,356
That's why you couldn't tell me, right?

323
00:15:58,844 --> 00:16:00,344
That's not it.

324
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:03,669
I kept thinking I'd tell you
once I found another job...

325
00:16:03,669 --> 00:16:06,152
and could stand a little taller.

326
00:16:06,485 --> 00:16:08,018
And before I knew it,
it had been this long.

327
00:16:16,648 --> 00:16:19,048
But why this place of all places?
It's far from the company.

328
00:16:19,869 --> 00:16:23,469
The CPO said to pick a place
that was tasty, comfortable, and I liked.

329
00:16:23,469 --> 00:16:25,339
- Right?
- Of course.

330
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:28,893
For me, this is that kind of place.
Tasty and comfortable.

331
00:16:29,370 --> 00:16:31,837
And it's right by my house,
so getting home is easy.

332
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,733
That was a very selfish choice.

333
00:16:35,683 --> 00:16:36,983
You really know how to talk.

334
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:41,200
Do you take lessons
on how to be unlikable?

335
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,200
It's just a fact.

336
00:16:42,785 --> 00:16:44,385
Eun Ae,

337
00:16:44,385 --> 00:16:47,818
do you take lessons on how to treat people
without boundaries?

338
00:16:48,157 --> 00:16:49,157
Sorry?

339
00:16:50,253 --> 00:16:52,353
Sometimes I'm surprised.

340
00:16:52,499 --> 00:16:54,999
How can you cross the line
with your superior...

341
00:16:54,999 --> 00:16:57,299
so casually?

342
00:16:58,648 --> 00:17:01,448
I'm pretty sure I warned you before.

343
00:17:01,929 --> 00:17:04,329
Warned her? I actually don't care.

344
00:17:06,997 --> 00:17:08,764
Manager Seo, you seem pretty drunk.

345
00:17:08,764 --> 00:17:10,464
Maybe you should stop drinking.

346
00:17:10,744 --> 00:17:14,177
What? I want to get drunk too.

347
00:17:14,669 --> 00:17:16,169
Manager, come on. Let's drink together.

348
00:17:16,539 --> 00:17:19,057
Let's all have a drink
for the greater good.

349
00:17:19,057 --> 00:17:20,057
I'll pour for you.

350
00:17:20,555 --> 00:17:22,455
Here, for our Chief Planning Officer.

351
00:17:23,616 --> 00:17:26,043
- And our Manager too...
- Just a little, please.

352
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,400
And our Team...

353
00:17:28,123 --> 00:17:29,600
Team Manager, you'll drink too, right?

354
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,920
- Yes, thank you.
- Yes.

355
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,700
It's my turn now.

356
00:17:39,512 --> 00:17:42,136
That's enough. Seo Seung Ri, get up.
Let's go home.

357
00:17:52,535 --> 00:17:54,875
Hey, Ko Gyeol! You...

358
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,744
Seung Ri.

359
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,325
Manager, are you okay?

360
00:18:09,325 --> 00:18:10,984
- Manager…
- Seung Ri, let's go.

361
00:18:10,984 --> 00:18:12,197
I'll take her home first.

362
00:18:12,352 --> 00:18:13,700
- Can you take care of the bill?
- Sure.

363
00:18:14,243 --> 00:18:15,276
The bill, please.

364
00:18:19,576 --> 00:18:22,616
Things are really tangled up.

365
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Excuse me?

366
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,568
I mean your traffic situation is a mess.
All four of you.

367
00:18:27,997 --> 00:18:28,997
What?

368
00:18:30,161 --> 00:18:31,161
Thank you for the meal.

369
00:18:32,301 --> 00:18:33,989
Come again next time.

370
00:18:34,384 --> 00:18:36,451
I'll give you lots of extras.

371
00:18:37,169 --> 00:18:38,469
Grandma, I'm heading home now.

372
00:18:38,469 --> 00:18:39,569
- Okay.
- Bye.

373
00:18:44,662 --> 00:18:46,662
You're the only one who doesn't know.

374
00:18:46,961 --> 00:18:48,294
You'll never know, not in this lifetime.

375
00:18:48,615 --> 00:18:51,400
Stop talking nonsense and clear the table.

376
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:53,525
Eun Ae is out there flying high.

377
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:57,740
I'm sorry, Dad.

378
00:18:59,657 --> 00:19:02,257
I never imagined
you'd be doing cleaning work.

379
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,500
What's wrong with cleaning?

380
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,800
It's honest work done with your own body.

381
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,133
I have no complaints about the job.

382
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,700
But Dad,

383
00:19:12,848 --> 00:19:14,948
whether you lost your job or not,

384
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:17,933
I can't let the beliefs and values
I've built up

385
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:19,371
collapse like that.

386
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:22,861
In the end, it wouldn't be good
for me or for the family.

387
00:19:24,317 --> 00:19:26,251
But you're the head of the family.

388
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:28,563
What about Bit Na and your wife?

389
00:19:32,475 --> 00:19:33,896
Grandpa!

390
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,300
My little puppy.

391
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,520
- Did you wake up?
- Yes.

392
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:45,088
Dad, were you crying?
Why are your eyes red?

393
00:19:45,088 --> 00:19:47,571
No, something just got in my eye.

394
00:19:48,792 --> 00:19:50,859
Bit Na will blow on it for you.

395
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,869
It feels better already.

396
00:19:56,091 --> 00:19:57,700
I'm the fixer, right?

397
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:00,877
Of course.
Bit Na is the best fixer in our family.

398
00:20:08,688 --> 00:20:09,724
That man...

399
00:20:10,985 --> 00:20:13,185
Did he apply for the loan or not?

400
00:20:15,459 --> 00:20:16,619
I'm home.

401
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:19,336
You're late. Did you eat?

402
00:20:19,643 --> 00:20:22,243
I ate with my co-workers
at Cho Rong's place.

403
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,000
What about Dad?

404
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,557
He went to your brother's house.

405
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,700
- Eun Ae.
- Yes?

406
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:36,667
That money you got
from the company sale...

407
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,233
you still have it, right?

408
00:20:38,935 --> 00:20:40,468
Of course. Why?

409
00:20:42,633 --> 00:20:44,900
It's nothing. Go upstairs and rest.

410
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:46,139
Okay, good night.

411
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:50,200
What am I even thinking?

412
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,691
I told her not to touch it
and keep it tied up tight.

413
00:20:55,843 --> 00:20:57,488
Why are you only coming now?

414
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,617
What happened? Did you apply for the loan?

415
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:02,901
Can you request your severance pay early?

416
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,397
Why aren't you answering?

417
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:14,368
What did you talk about with Eun Hyeong?

418
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:20,232
Say something.
Why are you keeping your mouth shut?

419
00:21:21,508 --> 00:21:23,277
Eun Hyeong says he absolutely can't do it.

420
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:26,925
If he's that firm in his decision,
what can we do?

421
00:21:27,216 --> 00:21:28,555
Are you really going to be like this?

422
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:32,400
Please, think about Eun Hyeong.

423
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,384
Even if he became a professor
by paying that donation,

424
00:21:35,672 --> 00:21:38,205
do you think he could teach students
with peace of mind even for a day?

425
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:40,733
It's just a university.

426
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:43,872
Why are we pushing him to sit
on thorns for the rest of his life?

427
00:21:44,021 --> 00:21:45,121
Cho Seong Jun.

428
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:47,376
If it's just because getting the money
is hard,

429
00:21:47,376 --> 00:21:49,333
I'll do it. I'll get it!

430
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:50,900
Wait...

431
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:01,613
Looks like you even took wedding photos
when you went out on your date.

432
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,533
They are not wedding photos.

433
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:07,100
They are the wedding photos.

434
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:11,600
We've lived together for over 50 years,
and I never even got to put a veil on her.

435
00:22:11,910 --> 00:22:12,977
I should at least do that much.

436
00:22:13,216 --> 00:22:15,133
But Father, wedding photos aside,

437
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:17,296
why did you take this solo portrait?

438
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:21,336
If you don't know, just stay quiet.

439
00:22:21,552 --> 00:22:24,933
Honestly, what do I not know...

440
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:29,859
Father, is this...

441
00:22:30,694 --> 00:22:33,561
Let's all go inside.
We should head in too.

442
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,800
Rest well.

443
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:39,133
You worked hard, Mr. Ju.

444
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:41,187
- Go inside, Father.
- Good night, Mother.

445
00:22:41,187 --> 00:22:43,443
Rest well, Chairman, Madam.

446
00:22:47,755 --> 00:22:51,688
You too, CEO and Madam.

447
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:58,963
These days, I really don't like Yong Man.

448
00:23:01,633 --> 00:23:02,700
Why the sigh?

449
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:06,643
Don't you know what that photo means?

450
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,293
It's Father's funeral portrait.

451
00:23:11,191 --> 00:23:12,324
A funeral portrait?

452
00:23:14,338 --> 00:23:15,405
That's what it is?

453
00:23:20,537 --> 00:23:22,470
He must have been really happy
about something...

454
00:23:23,856 --> 00:23:25,456
to smile so brightly.

455
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:32,300
Were you looking at the photo?

456
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:38,261
Yes. No matter how many times I see it,
it turned out well.

457
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,384
Let's set a day...

458
00:23:41,984 --> 00:23:43,351
and go see flowers together.

459
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,533
Gyeol found a really nice place.

460
00:23:46,775 --> 00:23:49,375
Are you sure you'll be okay to go?

461
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:52,685
Of course. I feel much better now.

462
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:56,233
Maybe because you've been taking
such good care of me.

463
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:59,500
Go to sleep. You must be tired.

464
00:24:15,069 --> 00:24:16,102
Why?

465
00:24:16,856 --> 00:24:18,701
Lie down with your head on my arm.

466
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,229
That's so embarrassing.

467
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:23,100
Come on.

468
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,600
It's been a long time
since I've lain down like this.

469
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,000
What?

470
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:55,000
That's the line from the first movie
we watched together,

471
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:58,433
"Heavenly Homecoming to Stars."

472
00:25:00,033 --> 00:25:01,600
Silly you.

473
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,633
It's been a long time
since I've lain down like this.

474
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:30,024
Seung Ri.

475
00:25:30,464 --> 00:25:31,697
I'm sorry.

476
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:33,364
- Let me help her lie down first.
- Yes, hurry inside.

477
00:25:33,364 --> 00:25:34,497
This way.

478
00:25:39,332 --> 00:25:41,032
Seo Seung Ri has that side to her?

479
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,200
Interesting.

480
00:25:46,859 --> 00:25:49,592
What happened? Why is she this drunk?

481
00:25:50,005 --> 00:25:53,187
I think it's from drinking makgeolli
on an empty stomach.

482
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,533
That's unusual.

483
00:25:54,933 --> 00:25:57,800
She never lets people see her drunk.

484
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,155
Come on out.
I'll bring something to drink.

485
00:26:00,155 --> 00:26:01,155
Okay.

486
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,500
Did the two of you drink alone?

487
00:26:27,499 --> 00:26:29,900
No, Gyeol and another co-worker
were there too.

488
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:33,333
You all grew up in one house,

489
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:36,600
and now you all ended up in one company.

490
00:26:37,433 --> 00:26:40,600
It's because of Gyeol, right?
That Seung Ri ended up like that.

491
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,733
- Let's go.
- Okay.

492
00:26:56,933 --> 00:26:59,611
The only place we can get money right now
is Eun Ae.

493
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:01,900
What should I do?

494
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:05,200
Mom.

495
00:27:07,389 --> 00:27:08,456
Why are you out here?

496
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,600
- Are you coming back from the library?
- Yes.

497
00:27:11,832 --> 00:27:13,532
Mom, is something bothering you?

498
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,399
No, what worries?

499
00:27:16,133 --> 00:27:18,433
Dr. Cho, stop worrying about other things

500
00:27:18,433 --> 00:27:19,800
and focus on preparing for your exam.

501
00:27:20,159 --> 00:27:22,159
Every time you see me, it's "exam."

502
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:24,300
Do you really want me
to become a doctor that badly?

503
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:25,300
Of course I do.

504
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:28,600
If you haven't eaten,
find something yourself.

505
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,400
What's wrong with her?

506
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:37,100
What do you mean?

507
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:41,000
I mean give your money to your brother.

508
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:42,300
Mom.

509
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,633
I'm not asking for it for free.
I'll pay it back somehow.

510
00:27:47,533 --> 00:27:49,805
If your brother doesn't get that money
right now,

511
00:27:49,805 --> 00:27:51,568
he'll lose the professorship
he finally got.

512
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:53,100
No.

513
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:54,900
What?

514
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:57,900
I'm not giving my money to Eun Hyeong.

515
00:27:57,900 --> 00:27:58,900
Eun Ae.

516
00:28:07,033 --> 00:28:09,533
(Our Happy Days)

517
00:28:09,928 --> 00:28:11,301
You're single,

518
00:28:11,301 --> 00:28:12,891
and you work at such a good company.

519
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:13,952
If he misses this chance, then forever...

520
00:28:13,952 --> 00:28:15,435
Why are you doing this to me?

521
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,800
As the eldest daughter,
can't you understand?

522
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,048
Then what am I to you?
Am I not your daughter?

523
00:28:20,048 --> 00:28:21,883
Not this pervert again!

524
00:28:21,883 --> 00:28:24,459
If I'm a pervert, then you're a thug.

525
00:28:24,459 --> 00:28:25,733
Just think simply.

526
00:28:25,733 --> 00:28:28,200
If you start over like that,
